+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MQ5UbvT8rsxX26L2ffquVe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear: `connectWs` waits for the 'open' event, then resolves with the WebSocket. Then `connectClient` awaits the first message. But the server sends the sync message on 'connection' — by the time `connectWs` resolves and `connectClient` then calls `waitForMessage`, the sync message has already been sent and received but not listened for yet (the 'message' handler wasn't attached yet).\n\nThe fix is to set up the message listener before the connection is fully established, or to combine connect + wait into one function:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1438,"cache_read_input_tokens":52416,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1438},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4507f320-b808-4e74-bda1-a4565da48d2e","uuid":"aa5fdfff-1bc4-4970-b554-62b6ecada5fe"}
